    <statement><p>Add or subtract the rational expressions to a single rational expression and then simplify. If applicable, state the restricted domain.</p>
<p><m>\displaystyle{{\frac{x}{x-8}-\frac{17x-72}{x^{2}-8x}} =}</m> <fillin characters="40" name="AnSwEr0001"/></p>
</statement>
    <answer>
      <p>
        <m>\frac{x-9}{x}, x\ne 8</m>
      </p>
    </answer>
    <solution><p><m>\displaystyle{\begin{aligned}
   {\frac{x}{x-8}-\frac{17x-72}{x^{2}-8x}} 
      \amp = {\frac{x}{x-8}}-\frac{{17x-72}}{x(x - 8)} \\
      \amp = \frac{x \cdot x}{({x-8}) \cdot x}-\frac{{17x-72}}{x(x - 8)} \\
      \amp = \frac{x^{2}}{x(x - 8)}-\frac{{17x-72}}{x(x - 8)} \\
      \amp = \frac{x^{2}-({17x-72})}{x(x - 8)} \\
      \amp = \frac{{x^{2}-17x+72}}{x(x - 8)} \\
      \amp = \frac{(x - 8)(x - 9)}{x(x - 8)} \\
      \amp = {\frac{x-9}{x}, x\ne 8}
\end{aligned}
    }</m></p>
<p>Since the factor <m>{x-8}</m> was canceled, the domain condition lost during the simplification is <m>x \ne {8}</m>.</p>
</solution>
